text: The Green Party of Sweden is a political party in Sweden. * The party supports renewable energy, animal rights, and feminism. * The party was founded as part of the anti-nuclear movement on 20 September 1981. * The party currently holds 16 out 349 seats in the Riksdag, 4 out of 20 seats in Sweden's European Parliament, 102 out of 1,597 County government seats and 732 out of 12,780 municipal government seats.
